The hurricane season in the Caribbean normally runs from June to November, but can occur any time of the year.
Potential Tropical Cyclone Nine, which may develop into a Tropical Storm, is currently forecast to bring hazardous sea and weather conditions to the islands from late Wednesday 29 - Thursday 30 July 2020.
You should monitor weather updates from the US National Hurricane Centre and the BVI Department of Disaster Management. Visitors should download the DDM alert app from the play store.
